Database

Media Manager 1.0 utilizes as the persistence in database JPA with Hibernate implementation technology.
Thus, it is possible to modify the choice of the database just modifying the configuration file.

The Version 1.0 has the configuration of two SQL databases, HSQLDB and PostgreSQL. The HSQLDB (HyperSQL)
is a database open sourcer developed using Java and do not need to be install. Already PostgreSQL 
is a more robust database and data needs to be installed on the machine before running the code. 
To learn more about installing PostgreSQL see (http://www.postgresql.org/download/).

To choose which configuration database should be used when running the Media Manager, do:

1º Configure the file "..\MediaManager\src\main\resources\hibernate.properties":

* HSQLDB:
  To use HSQLDB uncomment the code:
  
	# Configuração hsql
	hibernate.dialect=org.hibernate.dialect.HSQLDialect
	hibernate.connection.driver_class=org.hsqldb.jdbc.JDBCDriver
	hibernate.connection.url=jdbc:hsqldb:hsql://localhost/xdb
	hibernate.connection.username=SA
	hibernate.connection.password=
	
* PostgreSQL:
To use PostgreSQL uncomment the code:

	# Configuração PostgreSQL
	hibernate.dialect=org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQLDialect
	hibernate.connection.driver_class=org.postgresql.Driver
	hibernate.connection.url=jdbc:postgresql://127.10.138.2:5432/jbossews
	hibernate.connection.username=<username>
	hibernate.connection.password=<password>

2º Check the Listener "InitDBListener" in web.xml

* HSQLDB:
The listener must be uncommented so that the database be configured in the application execution.

	<listener>
		<listener> org.cruxframework.mediamanager.server.db.InitDBListener </ listener-class>
	</listener>

* PostgreSQL:

The listener is not necessary, so just commented it:
<!-- 
	<listener>
		<listener-class>org.cruxframework.mediamanager.server.db.InitDBListener</listener-class>
	</listener> 
-->